place.name: TRIMINGHAM
place.gazetteerText: TRIMINGHAM, a parish in Erpingham district, Norfolk; on the coast, 5½ miles N of North Walsham r. station. Post town, North Walsham, under Norwich. Acres, 680; of which 145 are water. Real property, £941. Pop., 185. Houses, 46. The manor belongs to Lord Suffield. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £140.* Patron, the Duchy of Lancaster. The church is plain. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
